his setting; others are defeated by it. Though literature infuses this social history of 19th-century Rio, it is replete with maps, graphs, non-fiction sources, and statistical data and analysis that are the historian's stock-in-trade. By connecting a literary understanding of the social problems with the quantitative data traditional historical methods provide, Frank creates a richer and deeper understanding of society in 19th-century Rio.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aBrazilian fictionzBrazilzRio de Janeiroy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and societyzBrazilzRio de JaneiroxHistoryy19th century. 4aRio de Janeiro. 4aliterary history. 4asocial history. 4aspatial history. 4aurban life. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804797306zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804797306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804797306.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles